dashboardItems.text:
**Big Catch-up Coverage Indicators**	

 _These visualizations provide a comprehensive view of RI and BCU data, including BCU doses distributed by age groups this year, under-one doses administered through RI the previous year, BCU coverage by age groups, and geographic coverage_
**Behavioural and Social Drivers of Vaccination (BeSD) Childhood Vaccination Indicators**

indicators.name: [CONFIG] EPI-BCU - BeSD: Affordability
indicators.numeratorDescription: Number of parents/caregivers reporting when asked “How easy is it to pay for vaccination, considering any payments to the clinic, the cost of getting there, plus the cost of taking time away from work?”

indicators.denominatorDescription: Number of parents/caregivers reporting Not at all easy; A little easy; Moderately easy; or Very easy when asked “How easy is it to pay for vaccination, considering any payments to the clinic, the cost of getting there, plus the cost of taking time away from work?”
indicators.description: Percentage of parents/caregivers who say vaccination is “moderately” or “very” easy to pay for
indicators.name: [CONFIG] EPI-BCU - BeSD: Affordability (%)
indicators.numeratorDescription: Number of parents/caregivers reporting Moderately easy; or Very easy when asked “How easy is it to pay for vaccination, considering any payments to the clinic, the cost of getting there, plus the cost of taking time away from work?”

indicators.name: [CONFIG] EPI-BCU - BeSD: Confidence in vaccine benefits
indicators.numeratorDescription: Number of parents/caregivers reporting when asked “How important do you think vaccines are for your child’s health?”

indicators.denominatorDescription: Number of parents/caregivers reporting Not at all important; A little important; Moderately important; or Very important when asked “How important do you think vaccines are for your child’s health?”
indicators.description: Percentage of parents/caregivers who say that vaccines are “moderately” or “very” important for their child’s health
indicators.name: [CONFIG] EPI-BCU - BeSD: Confidence in vaccine benefits (%)
indicators.numeratorDescription: Number of parents/caregivers reporting Moderately important; or Very important when asked “How important do you think vaccines are for your child’s health?”

indicators.name: [CONFIG] EPI-BCU - BeSD: Family norms
indicators.numeratorDescription: Number of parent parents/caregivers reporting when asked “Do you think most of your close family and friends want you to get your child vaccinated?”

indicators.denominatorDescription: Number of parent parents/caregivers reporting Yes or No when asked “Do you think most of your close family and friends want you to get your child vaccinated?”
indicators.description: Percentage of parents/caregivers who say most of their close family and friends want their child to be vaccinated
indicators.name: [CONFIG] EPI-BCU - BeSD: Family norms (%)
indicators.numeratorDescription: Number of parent parents/caregivers reporting Yes when asked “Do you think most of your close family and friends want you to get your child vaccinated?”

indicators.name: [CONFIG] EPI-BCU - BeSD: Intention to get vaccine
indicators.numeratorDescription: Number of parent parents/caregivers reporting when asked “Do you want your child to get none of these vaccines, some of these vaccines or all of these vaccines based on your country recommended vaccination schedule?”

indicators.denominatorDescription: Number of parents/caregivers reporting None; Some; or All when asked “Do you want your child to get none of these vaccines, some of these vaccines or all of these vaccines based on your country recommended vaccination schedule?”
indicators.description: Percentage of parents/caregivers who want their child to get “all” of the recommended vaccines
indicators.name: [CONFIG] EPI-BCU - BeSD: Intention to get vaccine (%)
indicators.numeratorDescription: Number of parent parents/caregivers reporting All when asked “Do you want your child to get none of these vaccines, some of these vaccines or all of these vaccines based on your country recommended vaccination schedule?”

indicators.name: [CONFIG] EPI-BCU - BeSD: Know where to get vaccination
indicators.numeratorDescription: Number of parents/caregivers reporting when asked “Do you know where to go to get your child vaccinated?”

indicators.denominatorDescription: Number of parents/caregivers reporting Yes or No when asked “Do you know where to go to get your child vaccinated?”
indicators.description: Percentage of parents/caregivers who know where to get their child vaccinated
indicators.name: [CONFIG] EPI-BCU - BeSD: Know where to get vaccination (%)
indicators.numeratorDescription: Number of parents/caregivers reporting Yes when asked “Do you know where to go to get your child vaccinated?”
